\pard\qc\sl360\slmult1\sb240\sa240\b\caps Definition of Terms\caps0\b0\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 Zero-Knowledge Proof: A cryptographic method that allows one party to prove a statement is true without revealing the private information used to prove it.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 Proof of Attendance: A digital record showing that a participant attended a specific event, session, or venue.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 Soulbound Attestation: A non-transferable credential issued to a wallet and intended to remain permanently associated with that wallet.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 Venue Hash: A cryptographic representation of approved event location values, including venue coordinates, allowed radius, and event identity.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 Event Binding: A security mechanism that ties a proof or signature to one specific event so it cannot be reused for another event.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 Sybil Resistance: A system property that limits a person from creating many fake or duplicate identities to gain unfair advantage.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 Subnet Verification: A technique that checks whether a request appears to originate from a network range associated with the event venue.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 Attestation: A signed on-chain statement issued by a trusted contract or account to confirm a claim about a user or event.\par\par 
