\pard\qc\sl360\slmult1\sb240\sa240\b\caps Chapter 3: System Methodology\caps0\b0\par\par 
\pard\ql\sl360\slmult1\sb120\sa120\b 3.1 Introduction\b0\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 This chapter presents the methodology that will guide the design, implementation, and evaluation of WiFiProof. It explains the research approach, development method, software tools, hardware requirements, and the rationale for selecting each approach.\par\par 
\pard\ql\sl360\slmult1\sb120\sa120\b 3.2 Research Methodology\b0\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 The project will use a design science and prototype-driven methodology supported by both qualitative and quantitative techniques.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1\li720\fi-360 - Qualitative approach: Literature review, analysis of existing attendance systems, and stakeholder-oriented requirements gathering from organizers and attendees.\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1\li720\fi-360 - Quantitative approach: Measurement of proof generation time, claim completion time, network verification success rate, and system responsiveness under concurrent use.\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1\li720\fi-360 - Artifact evaluation: The WiFiProof prototype itself serves as the research artifact and will be evaluated against security, privacy, and usability goals.\par 
\pard\ql\sl360\slmult1\sb120\sa120\b 3.3 System Development Methodology\b0\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1 The system will be developed using Agile methodology. Agile is suitable because WiFiProof combines several tightly connected components: a browser-based proving flow, a smart contract, API routes, organizer tooling, and external integrations. Incremental development allows each layer to be built, tested, and refined without blocking the entire project.\par\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1\li720\fi-360 - Planning and requirements analysis: Define system actors, event flows, privacy requirements, and threat model.\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1\li720\fi-360 - Design and prototyping: Model the organizer workflow, attendee claiming flow, and contract interfaces.\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1\li720\fi-360 - Iterative implementation: Build frontend components, proof generation package, and smart contracts in parallel.\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1\li720\fi-360 - Testing and refinement: Validate correctness, usability, and security using structured tests and user feedback.\par 
\pard\qj\sl360\slmult1\li720\fi-360 - Deployment preparation: Test on Base Sepolia and prepare for staged production deployment.\par 
